Bojan Krkic  underwent an operation in Barcelona on Wednesday as the Stoke City forward steps up his recuperation after suffering a cruciate knee ligament injury.

Former Barcelona striker Bojan, 24, went under the surgeon's knife at the Deixus hospital in Barcelona and Sportsmail understands that the operation - which lasted just under one hour and a half - went as planned.

He suffered the injury during Stoke's 4-1 victory at Rochdale in the FA Cup.

